### UI & Styling

- Prefer Expo built-ins (`View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, etc.) and `expo-image`.
- Use NativeWind utility classes for rapid UI; fallback to `StyleSheet.create` for perf-critical styles.
- Responsive layout: Flexbox + `useWindowDimensions` for breakpoints and conditional styles.
- Support dark mode via `useColorScheme`; expose theme helpers (see `hooks/use-theme-color.ts`).
- Ensure a11y: labels, roles, `accessibilityHint`, proper semantics for interactives.

### Examples

```tsx
// Example component structure and theming
export function ExampleCard(props: { title: string; onPress: () => void }) {
  return (
    <Pressable accessibilityRole="button" className="rounded-xl p-4 bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900" onPress={props.onPress}>
      <Text className="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 text-base font-semibold">{props.title}</Text>
    </Pressable>
  );
}
```

